Clarifying the misconception first: it's not the LAN that matters — it's the transport. `claude_desktop_config.json` only validates **stdio** servers (command/args). Claude Desktop doesn't accept a raw remote `url` there — if you put a `url`/`type: "http"` field in, Desktop can silently corrupt the config. Those `url` entries are a Claude *Code* thing, not Desktop. LAN vs public is irrelevant to that; your Mac just has to resolve `*.ash4d.com` → 192.168.7.150, which it does.

So you have two working paths:

**1. Custom Connector UI** — what you already did for `mcp-memory`. Paste the HTTPS URL; it handles the streamable-http transport natively. LAN URLs are fine. Simplest.

**2. The JSON route you're asking about** — you don't hand-write a remote URL; you wrap each endpoint with the `mcp-remote` stdio bridge:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "sme-salesengineer": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "https://mcp-sme-salesengineer.ash4d.com/mcp"]
    },
    "sme-salesengineer-manager": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "https://mcp-sme-salesengineer-manager.ash4d.com/mcp"]
    }
  }
}
```

Notes:

- **Merge** these into your existing `mcpServers` block (you already have stdio entries like `ollama-code` there) — don't overwrite it.
- File location: `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`. Restart Claude Desktop after saving.
- Requires Node/`npx` on your Mac (you have it — ollama-code runs via npx).
- No auth args needed since the endpoints are unauthenticated. If a connection fails during the SSE probe, force the transport: add `"--transport", "http-only"` to the args.

Either path lands the same three tools (`recall`, `save`, `memory_status`) per domain. Given you already used the connector UI for `mcp-memory`, that's the lower-friction choice; use the JSON if you'd rather keep all your servers in one config file.

Sources: [Fix: HTTP MCP Server URL Won't Connect in Claude Desktop](https://startdebugging.net/2026/05/fix-http-mcp-server-url-wont-connect-in-claude-desktop/), [Claude Desktop silently destroys config when MCP server uses url field (#37286)](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/37286), [MCP connector — Claude Platform Docs](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/agents-and-tools/mcp-connector)

